content:
To convert a string of text into JSON format using an HTML page, you can use JavaScript. Here's a simple example of how you can achieve this. In this example, we'll use a basic HTML structure with embedded JavaScript to convert a given string into a JSON object:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>String to JSON Conversion</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        pre {
            background-color: #f8f8f8;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Convert String to JSON</h1>
    <button onclick="convertToJson()">Convert</button>
    <pre id="jsonOutput"></pre>

    <script>
        function convertToJson() {
            const text = "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Proin tempor metus sed lectus iaculis ultricies. Pellentesque quis magna quis est commodo euismod ut vel mi. Vivamus dapibus, velit vel commodo dignissim, sapien nibh faucibus nibh, sit amet pretium ex tortor ut nunc. Sed auctor nulla ut commodo hendrerit. Sed varius lobortis enim, at sagittis lectus mollis vel. Sed eu leo et nunc auctor commodo in id mi. Nullam eu velit ipsum. Sed quis urna commodo, pellentesque arcu sed, finibus justo. Quisque malesuada orci et commodo luctus. Morbi vel massa commodo, faucibus metus sed, lacinia mauris.";

            // Create a JSON object with the text
            const jsonObject = {
                text: text
            };

            // Convert the JSON object to a string for display
            const jsonString = JSON.stringify(jsonObject, null, 2);

            // Display the JSON string in the preformatted text area
            document.getElementById('jsonOutput').textContent = jsonString;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **HTML Structure**: This structure includes a button to trigger the conversion and a `pre` element to display the JSON output.
- **JavaScript Function**: The `convertToJson` function takes the given text and creates a JSON object with it. It then converts the JSON object into a string using `JSON.stringify`, which is formatted for readability with the `null` and `2` parameters (pretty printing with 2 spaces).
- **Displaying JSON**: The resulting JSON string is inserted into the `pre` element, where it is displayed as formatted text.

When you open this HTML page in a browser and click the "Convert" button, the string will be converted into a JSON format and displayed on the page.
